 rapidly.\r\n- LEAN METHODOLOGY\r\n•	Eliminate waste\r\n•	Build quality in\r\n•	Create knowledge\r\n•	Defer commitment\r\n•	Deliver fast\r\n•	Respect people\r\n•	Optimize the whole\r\n4. Do you have a cross-functional team?\r\n- then we prefer you to choose SCRUM\r\n5. Are you facing challenges?\r\nWhen it comes to deal with different interests that need to go in the same direction using an AGILE style, definitely you are facing many challenges. Some of them are predictable but some others are not. Learn from real experiences and discover great tips for an effective AGILE implementation, productivity and a functional communication across the team.\r\n6. Agile vs Waterfall\r\nIf you have a small and less complex project with the level of integration with external system is simple or not needed where for the market, rapid development is needed and can have limited feature set also the customer availability is frequent in the duration of project and the customer’s tolerance for scope and cost changes are flexible in budget and schedule is possible and welcome then AGILE is the proper decision otherwise WATERFALL.', 'admin', '');
